title: Tear gas and stun grenades won't stop protests as long as fear persists in Paris
description: Thousands of people crowded onto the streets of Nanterre, many holding banners or placards, demanding "justice for Nahel".

title: Mother and seven-year-old child rescued after falling overboard from ferry
description: A woman and her seven-year-old child have reportedly been rescued after falling overboard from a ferry travelling from Sweden to Poland.

title: Italian police blame man from England for Colosseum graffiti
description: Italian police have identified a man from England as the likely culprit after graffiti was scribbled on a wall at the Colosseum - sparking widespread anger.

title: France stops public transport and deploys 40,000 officers amid fears of third night of rioting
description: France is set to deploy 40,000 officers on Thursday evening amid fears of a third night of rioting in the capital triggered by the fatal police shooting of a 17-year-old boy.

title: Virgin Galactic completes first commercial flight into space
description: Virgin Galactic has completed its first commercial flight into space.

title: Satellite images show smoke from Canada wildfires across UK - as fresh alerts issued in US
description: Satellite images have picked up an area of smoke lying across the UK which can be traced back to wildfires in North America, according to the Met Office.

title: 'Our new love': Chrissy Teigen and John Legend welcome fourth child - named after surrogate mother
description: Chrissy Teigen and John Legend have announced the birth of their fourth child, a baby boy, via surrogacy.

title: Sweetener commonly used in Diet Coke and other products 'to be listed as cancer risk'
description: A sweetener commonly used in Diet Coke and other products is set to be declared as a potential cancer risk, according to reports.

title: Why are people protesting in France - and why is there a history of rioting?
description: Riots have broken out in Paris and other French cities after a teenage boy was shot dead by police during a traffic stop.

title: HRT used for menopause linked to dementia - but it may not be due to the treatment
description: The use of hormone replacement therapy (HRT) to ease the effects of menopause has been associated with a higher risk of dementia, a new study has found - but the link between the two may not be down to the treatment.

title: 'This whole place is going up': Police killing of teen is catalyst for wanton destruction in France
description: It was past 2am when the fires and disorder of Nanterre came to our doorstep and lit up the sky, bringing devastation in its wake. This is a corner of France where anger and anarchy have taken a grip.

title: Plane makes emergency landing after nose wheels fail to come down
description: A Delta flight was forced to do an emergency landing after the nose landing gear failed to come down.

title: Unrest spreads in France over fatal police shooting of teenager
description: Protests and riots over the fatal police shooting of a teenager in Paris have continued for a second night - and spread to other cities in France.
